message.content: cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MED, cs.AI, cs.NEURON - The paper presents an automated method for analyzing cardiovascular magnetic resonance (CMR) images using deep neural networks, specifically a fully convolutional network (FCN). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of a large-scale annotated dataset and the evaluation of technical and clinically relevant metrics, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.MED (Medical Imaging). Additionally, the use of deep neural networks for image segmentation and pattern recognition is a common theme in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NEURON (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
